@NODE Introduction
@TITLE "cpumonitor · Introduction"


    @{b}Introduction@{ub}


    CPU Monitor is a small utility which shows CPU usage
    statistic.
    

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements
@TITLE "cpumonitor · Requirements"


    @{b}Requirements@{ub}


    - MorphOS 1.4

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation
@TITLE "cpumonitor · Installation"


    @{b}Installation@{ub}


    Copy CPU Monitor to a place you like.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Startup
@TITLE "cpumonitor · Startup"


    @{b}Startup@{ub}

    
    You can start CPU Monitor from Ambient or from the
    CLI.
 

    @{b}Ambient@{ub}

    CPU Monitor supports all default MUI- and Commodity-
    tooltypes.

    Additionally it supports following tooltypes:

        DONOTACTIVATE - on start the CPU Monitor
                        window will not be activated

        NOSIZEGADGET  - the CPU Monitor window will
                        opened w/o SizeGadget.

          TIP: Place the window to the place you like, re-
          size it how you want it, then snapshot the window
          using MUI's snapshot feature. Now restart CPU
          Monitor with activated NOSIZEGADGET tooltype.

        BORDERLESS    - no windowborders. this also
                        activates the 'newlook' which
                        offers hidable customgadgets
                        for dragging and resizing.

        DNETCFILTER   - filters out cpu usage of task "dnetc
                        crunch #1", so CPU Monitor becomes a 
                        bit more useful, when dnetc is
                        running.

    @{b}CLI@{ub}

    It has no options. Just start it.

@ENDNODE


@NODE MainWindow
@TITLE "cpumonitor · Main window"


    @{b}Main window@{ub}


    Err... no user input is required. Just watch.

@ENDNODE

@NODE MenuOptions
@TITLE "cpumonitor · Menuoptions"


    @{b}Menu options@{ub}


    @{b}Project@{ub}

        About...

            Opens the About window with copyright information and
            credits.

        About MUI...

            Opens MUIs About window.

        Quit

            Quits CPU Monitor immediatelly.


    @{b}Settings:@{ub}

        Locked

            When CPU Monitor was invoked with the "BORDERLESS"
            tooltype then you can dissable the custom gadgets
            for dragging and sizing with this menuitem.

        Snapshot
        Unsnapshot

            Snapshots or unsnapshots CPU Monitors main window,
            useful when running in BORDERLESS mode.

        MUI...

            Opens MUI Settings. Here you can define the look
            of CPU Monitor.

            List of possible changes which may be hard to find:

                CPU usage display frame
                    -> Strings/Textfield

                Size-/Drag-/Windowframe in BORDERLESS mode
                    -> Button/ImageButton

                Space between Windowborder and display
                    -> Window/BorderSpacing

                Space between Windowborder and display in
                BORDERLESS mode
                    -> Button/ImageButton/Framespacing

                Size-/Drag-/Window background in BORDERLESS
                mode
                    -> Window/Background

@ENDNODE


